==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Somatic
<hw>So*mat"ic</hw> <pr>(s⟦osl⟧*m⟦acr⟧t"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>swmatiko`s</grk>, fr. <grk>sw^ma</grk> the body.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the body as a whole; corporeal;
<as>as, <ex>somatic</ex> death; <ex>somatic</ex> changes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the wall of the body;
somatopleuric; parietal; <as>as, the <ex>somatic</ex> stalk of the yolk
sac of an embryo</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Somatic death</b></col>. <cd>See the Note under
<er>Death</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 1.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Somatical</ent>⟦br⟧
